 of promotion is fair enough.&quot;<br><br>The second broadcast irritated the hell out of me.  I don't care for the Legends server concept, and having it forced down my throat just hacks me off even more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urnrkaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RNR Kaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 11:11:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4523.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Serverwide Ads</span><hr size=1> The really irritating thing to me is that this service should be for all servers.  <br><br>VI has 400,000+/-  customers that pay 10$ a month to satisfy.  Instead of having gm events and interesting stuff in game for all these customers they have put their time into making it only for those that will pay them MORE money.  IMO this is blatant thievery.  Why you ask?<br><br>When the game was released they promised continued in-game activity and events.  I don't know about ya'll, but I haven't seen one for a year.  Well now you will see even fewer...why?  because they are focusing on keeping the &quot;legends&quot; people happy.  A stupid mistake imo.  They are trying to give this server a feeling of a &quot;community&quot; whereas that leaves us feeling like we're thrown on the streets eating others leftovers.<br><br>marketing...  Appease those few 8000 people to piss off the other 392,000 that deserve every bit of that pie also.  Their goal in doing this?  eventually turn every server into a &quot;legends&quot; server that is 39.95 a month.  speculation, yes.  unrealistic?  I don't think so.<br><br>&quot;O God, thy ocean is so great, yet my boat is so small.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ur